    "raw_text": "Army Heritage Center Foundation:\n250 years of Army Soldier Stories\nThe Army Heritage Center Foundation shares the stories of U.S. Army soldiers from all eras, fostering understanding and building meaningful connections between the military and civilian communities. We accomplish this through public outreach activities like community-building, resource-sharing, education, and philanthropic investments in the preservation of Army history. As a private, nonprofit, non-Federal entity, AHCF is not affiliated with the Department of Defense and has no governmental status.\nAbout the Foundation\nAbout Us - Video\nOur Primary Beneficiary: The U.S. Army Heritage and Education Center\nThe U.S. Army Heritage and Education Center collects, preserves, and presents materials related to the evolution and application of landpower, as well as the experiences of American Soldiers, to build a foundation for strategic thought and to connect the public to the United States Army.\nLearn More\nUpcoming Events\nGive\nto Honor the American Soldier\nThe Army Heritage Center Foundation depends on the generosity of our donors to fulfill our mission. Donate today and join us in honoring the heritage of the American Soldier. Together, we can cultivate a world that invests in the preservation of soldier stories–and learns from them.\nDonate Now\nSubscribe for Updates\nSubscribe to stay informed about Foundation news, events and initiatives.\nFirst\nLast\nEmail",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "This is not a legislator press release. It is promotional content from the Army Heritage Center Foundation, a private nonprofit organization based in Pennsylvania that supports the U.S. Army Heritage and Education Center. The content describes the organization's mission, solicits donations, and invites newsletter subscriptions.",
