  {
    "title": "House Democrats Continue Disregard for Safety of Pennsylvania’s Female Athletes",
    "url": "http://RepGleim.com/News/38160/Press-Releases/House-Democrats-Continue-Disregard-for-Safety-of-Pennsylvania-s-Female-Athletes",
    "date": null,
    "raw_text": "House Democrats Continue Disregard for Safety of Pennsylvania’s Female Athletes\nJune 17, 2026\nHARRISBURG – State Rep. Barb Gleim (R-Cumberland) condemned Tuesday’s House Health Committee partisan vote to yet again re-refer\nHouse Bill 158\n,\nSenate Bill 9\nand\nHouse Bill 1849\nto the House Judiciary Committee. “This is nothing more than the latest attempt to avoid a public vote on protecting girls’ and women’s sports,” said Gleim.\nConsideration of House Bill 1849 has now been delayed for more than three months since its introduction, Senate Bill 9 has been awaiting House action for more than a year, and House Bill 158 has been stalled in committee for more than 16 months.\n“Yesterday’s actions are about delay and not policy,“ Gleim added. “Pennsylvania’s girls, parents, coaches and athletes deserve the opportunity to have their voices heard. Instead, House Democrats chose procedural gamesmanship over transparency and accountability.”\nThe re-referral is particularly troubling because both the House Health and Judiciary committees will have seen these bills twice, calling into question the sincerity of their previous statements.\n“Female athletes should not be forced to sacrifice opportunities that countless women have fought to secure,” Gleim commented.  “I will continue working to advance these bills and ensure the voices of Pennsylvania’s female athletes are not ignored.”\nRepresentative Barb Gleim\n199th Legislative District\nPennsylvania House of Representatives\nMedia Contact: Scott Little\n717-260-6137\nslittle@pahousegop.com\nRepGleim.com / Facebook.com/RepGleim\nShare\nSign Up to Receive Legislative Email Updates\nKeep up-to-date on the latest legislative and community news. Your email address will be used strictly for legislative purposes.\nEmail*\nZIP Code\nSubscribe",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Republican State Rep. Barb Gleim issued a statement criticizing the House Health Committee's vote to re-refer three bills related to transgender athlete participation in women's sports to the House Judiciary Committee. The bills, which would restrict transgender women and girls from competing in female sports categories, have been pending in committee for periods ranging from three months to over 16 months. No new legislation was introduced or passed; this release concerns a committee procedural vote.",
      "action_type": "statement",
      "topics": [
        "public_safety",
        "other"
      ],
      "spin_flag": true
    }
  },
