    "raw_text": "Gleim, Owlett: U.S. Supreme Court Backs Basic Biology in Groundbreaking Ruling\nJune 30, 2026\nHARRISBURG - The U.S. Supreme Court today echoed the country’s overwhelming public position that men should not be permitted to compete alongside girls in sports designated for women only. According to state Reps. Barb Gleim (R-Cumberland) and Clint Owlett (R-Tioga/Bradford), the 6-3 decision and corresponding court opinion also offered an extremely important distinction – that biological sex, not “gender identity,” should be the determining and distinguishing factor for separating sports.\nThe groundbreaking ruling confirms that states have the authority and responsibility to protect female athletes. While Gov. Josh Shapiro and House Democrats constantly dodge and duck the issue, the Supreme Court is confirming that Pennsylvania’s governing athletic body, the PIAA (Pennsylvania Interscholastic Athletic Association), and local school directors should be compelled to step in and restore sanity.\n“We’re calling on the PIAA and school boards across the Commonwealth, who have not already acted to protect their girl athletes, to enact policies now,” said Owlett. “We are thankful for the nearly two dozen school districts here in Pennsylvania and the 27 states nationwide who have taken seriously protection of our girl athletes.”\nProtecting girls’ sports has long been fought for via House Republican legislation. Gleim’s original House Bill 972 of 2021, legislation that would have ensured fairness for girl athletes, passed both chambers of the General Assembly in bipartisan fashion, only to be vetoed by Democrat Gov. Tom Wolf. Several similar bills which have been introduced this session -\nSenate Bill 9\n, which passed with bipartisan support;\nHouse Bill 1849\nand\nSenate Bill 1293\n- have been summarily sidestepped by House Democrats to prevent a vote.\n“This is a momentous decision for girls and women who have fought long and hard for fairness in sports,” said Gleim. “Because of the Democrats’ inaction, the ball is now in the PIAA’s court. It’s finally time to reinstitute fairness, protect our girl athletes, and affirm biological reality.”\nRepresentative Barb Gleim\n199th Legislative District\nPennsylvania House of Representatives\nMedia Contact: Scott Little\n717-260-6137\nslittle@pahousegop.com\nRepGleim.com / Facebook.com/RepGleim\nShare\nSign Up to Receive Legislative Email Updates\nKeep up-to-date on the latest legislative and community news. Your email address will be used strictly for legislative purposes.\nEmail*\nZIP Code\nSubscribe",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Pennsylvania state Representatives Barb Gleim and Clint Owlett issued a statement responding to a U.S. Supreme Court ruling on transgender athlete participation in sports, calling on the PIAA and local school boards to adopt policies restricting transgender girls from competing in girls' sports. They highlighted previously introduced legislation on the topic, including bills that passed one or both chambers but were vetoed or blocked from a floor vote.",
